WLC_EVENT_SOURCE_TIMER_UPDATE(3)                              WLC API FUNCITONS

NAME

    wlc_event_source_timer_update - set the delay for timer activation

SYNOPSIS

    void wlc_event_source_timer_update(struct wlc_event_source *source, 
                                       uint32_t ms_delay);

DESCRIPTION

    For a given source, wlc_event_source_timer_update() sets a time in ms
    according to ms_delay.  This will prime the timer added in the
    wlc_event_loop_add_timer(3) function which is triggered once the delay
    reaches zero.

    Setting a ms_delay of zero will disarm the event source.

RETURN VALUE

    None.

ALSO SEE

    wlc_event_loop_add_timer(3), wlc_event_source_remove(3)
